				\begin{document}$$\frac{d\rho }{dt}=-i[{ {\mathcal H} }_{S},\rho (t)]+\sum _{\alpha }\,{ {\mathcal L} }_{\alpha }\,[\rho (t)],$$\end{document}where complete positivity (i.e. physical) evolution is guaranteed43. Here, diagonal elements of the density matrix correspond to the populations of the different energy levels in the system. The advantage of this formalism is that it allows to easily change the transition rates to accommodate for different scenarios. All numerical simulation were erformed using the QuTiP python package44.
